<tr><td class='easySpoilerRow' colspan='2' style=''><div id='spoilerDiv71728003' class='easySpoilerSpoils'  style='display:none; white-space:wrap; overflow:auto; vertical-align:middle;'>
</p>
<p>1. Kf5! Now the bishop must move, and then 2. h8=Q+ Bb8 3. Qh1#</p>
<p>Note that the king&#8217;s waiting move must be to f5. Moving to a black square leaves him vulnerable to a check; moving to the h-file blocks the queen&#8217;s access to h1; and moving to f3 blocks the queen&#8217;s final checkmate.</p>
<p>If 1. Kf5 Be5 then 2. h8=Q+ Bxh8 3. f8=Q#.</p>
<p>From <em>Eskilstuna-Kuriren</em>, 1931.</p>
<p>
